						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall of the Akhilāṇḍēśvari shrine, in the Śikhānāthasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>This inscription in Sanskrit verse engraved in Grantha characters of about the 12th-13th centuries A.D., records the building of a <hi rend="italic">vimāna</hi> for the shrine for goddess Pārvati by Sundarēśa.</p>						

						</summary>
